    correctChoice: 
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  _50pointQ:
  - questionInfo: "An elderly patient is diagnosed with aggressive non-Hodgkin\u2019s 
      lymphoma. the tumor cells are shown to stain strongly for the CD20  marker.
      Which of the following biologic agents can be added to this  patient\u2019s
      chemotherapy regimen to help improve the treatment  response? "
    questionChoices:
    - Infliximab
    - Rituximab
    - Interleukin-2
    - Imatinib
    correctChoice: Rituximab
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: A group of investigators examined the effects of different muscarinic 
      agonists and antagonists on the bladder musculature. The curves  presented
      below were constructed after application of different agents.  Curve A represents
      the effect of bethanechol, a pure cholinergic  agonist. Which of the curves
      most likely represents the effect of  bethanechol after application of a reversible
      competitive antagonist?
    questionChoices:
    - Curve D
    - Curve B
    - Curve C
    - Curve E
    correctChoice: Curve E
    questionImage: {fileID: 21300000, guid: 60ecafdf1113fa447acf78a70a773e95, type: 3}
  - questionInfo: 23-year-old man is brought to the emergency department due to 
      weakness and confusion. Family members reported that for the last two  weeks
      he has experienced polyuria, polydipsia and increased appetite.  Medical history
      is remarkable for an appendectomy at age 12. He also  has a brother with hypothyroidism.
      On examination the patient is  lethargic and confused, but response to basic
      commands. His breath  has a fruity order. This patient is most likely deficient
      in a hormone that  normally performs which of the following actions.
    questionChoices:
    - decrease muscle protein synthesis
    - Facilitates the action of glucagon
    - Increases renal glucose reabsorption
    - Decreases glucagon secretion
    correctChoice: Decreases glucagon secretion
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: A 26-year-old previously healthy man is brought to the emergency 
      department following a motorbike accident. He is found to have a  maxillofacial
      injury. His condition is stabilized, and surgical repair is  performed. While
      recovering, the patient develops difficulty chewing  food. On examination,
      the jaw deviates to the right side when the  patient is instructed to open
      his mouth. The nerve that has been  injured in this patient exits the skull
      through which of the following  foramina?
    questionChoices:
    - Foramen spinosum
    - Foramen rotundum
    - Foramen ovale
    - Jugular foramen
    correctChoice: Foramen ovale
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: 'A 6-month-old baby is brought to the emergency department by his 
      mother because of recent onset of vomiting, irritability, and jaundice.  The
      infant was born at term and had been healthy until the onset of the  symptoms.
      All of his vaccinations are up to date. He had been breasted  exclusively until
      one week ago when cereals and fruit juice were  introduced into his diet. Further
      evaluation reveals hepatomegaly and  normal liver function tests, which of
      the following enzymes is most likely  to be deficient in this patient:'
    questionChoices:
    - Galactose-1-phosphate uridyl transferase
    - Aldolase B
    - 'Fructokinase '
    - Galactokinase
    correctChoice: Aldolase B
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: A 48-year-old man presents to the office because of perineal pain
      for the past 4  months. He states that the pain is dull, constant and has been
      interfering with  daily activities. He also reports mild pain during urination
      but denies urinary  frequency, urgency or straining. Past medical history is
      significant for migraine  headaches. Family history is unremarkable. Vitals
      are within normal limits.  Physical examination including digital rectal examination
      is normal. There is no  suprapubic pain on palpation. Urinalysis shows no abnormality.
      Expressed  prostatic secretion shows 2 leukocytes/hpf, but culture does not
      grow a  pathogenic organism. What is the most likely diagnosis in this patient?
    questionChoices:
    - Cystitis
    - Chronic bacterial prostatitis
    - Acute prostatitis
    - 'Chronic abacterial prostatitis '
    correctChoice: 'Chronic abacterial prostatitis '
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: The intracellular concentration of ion Z is 100 milliequivalents
      per liter  (mEq/L), and the extracellular concentration is 5 mEq/L. The molecular 
      weight of molecule Z is ~40 daltons. This relatively high intracellular  concentration
      of molecule Z is best explained by which of the following?
    questionChoices:
    - Extracellular assembly
    - Facilitative diffusion
    - Intracellular production
    - Primary active transport
    correctChoice: Primary active transport
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: 'A hypersensitivity reaction due to antibodies against group A
      streptococcal  antigens, these antibodies are cross reactive with host antigens
      in the heart,  brain, joints and skin. One of the following is not a major
      criterion for  diagnosing the described condition: '
    questionChoices:
    - Erythema marginatum
    - Prolonged PR interval
    - Sydenham chorea
    - Myocarditis
    correctChoice: Prolonged PR interval
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: A 70-year-old man develops the acute onset of an inability to speak. 
      Examination reveals that he struggles to pronounce a complete word and  cannot
      string words together. He is unable to repeat a sentence but can  follow simple
      and multistep commands. What is the most likely diagnosis?
    questionChoices:
    - 'Global aphasia '
    - 'Conduction aphasia '
    - Broca aphasia
    - Wernicke aphasia
    correctChoice: Broca aphasia
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: 45-year-old women presents to her physician with a two day history
      of  right upper quadrant pain, gas, and vomiting. She reports that her  symptoms
      are worse after she eats a fatty meal which of the following  substances inhibits
      the hormone, causing her right upper quadrant pain.
    questionChoices:
    - Cholycystokinin
    - 'Gastrin '
    - Pepsin
    - Somatostatin
    correctChoice: Somatostatin
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: 'The abnormal cleavage of mannose residues during the post translational
      processing of glycoproteins has been shown to result in  the development of
      a lupus-like autoimmune disease in mice. The  abnormal cleavage is due to a
      mutation of the enzyme -mannosidase II.  Based on your understanding of the
      processing of membrane proteins,  you would predict this enzyme to be localized
      to the:'
    questionChoices:
    - Peroxisome
    - Cytosol
    - Golgi apparatus
    - Lysosomes
    correctChoice: Golgi apparatus
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: A 23-year-old woman comes to the labor and delivery unit in active
      labor. An  hour later, she gives birth to a stillborn infant. The patient states
      that she did  not receive consistent prenatal care. An autopsy of the infant
      reveals cyclopia  and cleft palate. Examination of the brain shows fused cerebral
      hemispheres.  This condition was most likely caused by failure of differentiation
      of which of  the following anatomical structures?
    questionChoices:
    - Prosencephalon
    - Diencephalon
    - Myelencephalon
    - Mesencephalon
    correctChoice: Prosencephalon
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  _10pointQ:
  - questionInfo: "Who is credited with the saying \u201Cthe end justifies the means\u201D?"
    questionChoices:
    - Machiavelli
    - Nietzsche
    - Martin Luther king
    - Aristotle
    correctChoice: Machiavelli
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: What is the name of the device used to measure wind speed?
    questionChoices:
    - Hydrometer
    - Barometer
    - Thermometer
    - Anemometer
    correctChoice: Anemometer
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: 'The greatest expansion of the Islamic state occurred during the
      caliphate of:'
    questionChoices:
    - 'Hisham ibn Abd al-Malik '
    - 'Al-Walid ibn Abd al-Malik   '
    - 'Muawiya ibn Abi Sufyan '
    - 'Harun al-Rashid '
    correctChoice: 'Al-Walid ibn Abd al-Malik   '
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: Who discovered penicillin?
    questionChoices:
    - 'Alexander Fleming '
    - 'Rosalind Franklin   '
    - 'Louis Pasteur   '
    - 'Robert Koch '
    correctChoice: 'Alexander Fleming '
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  quizUIobj: {fileID: 609381636}
  timerObj: {fileID: 1981497918}
